title: Steely Dan - Discography 1972-1980 FLAC SHM-CD 2008
description:
Steely Dan - Discography 1972-1980 FLAC SHM-CD 2008

Steely Dan is an American jazz rock band founded by core members Walter Becker and Donald Fagen. 

The band's popularity peaked in the late 1970's, and their seven albums over that period of time blended elements of jazz, rock, funk, R&B, and pop.

Rolling Stone has called them "the perfect musical antiheroes for the Seventies".

1972 - Can't Buy A Thrill
1973 - Countdown To Ecstasy
1974 - Pretzel Logic
1975 - Katy Lied
1976 - The Royal Scam
1977 - Aja
1980 - Gaucho
